1	//axhob_operation
2	{rbtgo_director_divest}
3	
4	NOTE: This operation divests a {rbtr_director} {giam_service_account} from the {rbtgi_depot_project}.
5	The {rbtr_governor} reads the role's installed RBRA, extracts the SA email from the `client_email` field, issues a REST DELETE against the IAM API, and removes the production RBRA file from disk to mirror cloud state and prevent stale-credential reuse.
6	No arguments required; the target SA is derived entirely from the kindled regime and the role's installed credential file.
7	
8	//axhos_step
9	. *Authenticate as
10	{rbtr_governor}*:
11	.. Execute
12	{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
13	.. {rbbc_store}
14	`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
15	
16	//axhos_step
17	. *Read Role RBRA and Extract Service Account Email*:
18	.. {rbbc_require}
19	the role's installed RBRA file exists at
20	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
21	.. {rbbc_fatal}
22	if the file is missing: "Director RBRA file not found — director may not have been invested"
23	.. {rbbc_store}
24	`«SA_EMAIL»` from the `client_email` field of
25	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
26	.. {rbbc_fatal}
27	if `client_email` is empty or absent: "Director RBRA file present but client_email field is missing or empty"
28	
29	//axhos_step
30	. *Divest Director Service Account*:
31	.. {rbbc_call}
32	link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.delete] with:
33	... method: `DELETE`
34	... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts/«SA_EMAIL»`
35	... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
36	.. {rbbc_require}
37	HTTP 200 response OR HTTP 404 (already divested)
38	.. {rbbc_warn}
39	if HTTP 404: "Service account not found (already divested)"
40	
41	//axhos_step
42	. *Remove Production RBRA File*:
43	.. Remove the role's RBRA file at
44	{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
45	from disk
46	.. {rbbc_fatal}
47	if the file cannot be removed: "Failed to remove director RBRA file — manual cleanup required"
48	.. NOTE: Removing the RBRA file mirrors cloud state locally and prevents any process from reusing a credential that no longer corresponds to an active
49	{giam_service_account}.
50	
51	//axhos_step
52	. *Display Result*:
53	.. {rbbc_show}
54	single-line success naming `«SA_EMAIL»` and confirming the
55	{rbtr_director}
56	{giam_service_account}
57	was divested, or a notice that it was already absent
58	
59	//axhoc_completion
60	Successful execution removes the
61	{rbtr_director}
62	{giam_service_account}
63	from
64	{rbtgi_depot_project}
65	and deletes the local RBRA credential file.
66	Cloud state and local credential state are left in agreement: no stale key file remains after a successful divest.
67	A 404 response from the cloud DELETE is accepted as success — the
68	{giam_service_account}
69	is absent either way, and the RBRA file is removed regardless.
70

